Summary: The document contains a timetable for the first and second semesters of the MTech SE program, with courses such as Software Analysis & Design, Software Design Patterns, and Essential Practices for Agile Teams. The classes will be held on Saturdays from 9:00am to 5:30pm, with some evening classes on Tuesdays and Thursdays. The timetable also includes a course on DevSecOps Engineering and Automation, and the program is set to begin on January 11, 2025.

The AY2024/2025 Semester 2 Exam Timetable for MTech SE students includes exams for various courses such as EBA5003 Customer Analytics, ISY5004 Intelligent Sensing Systems, SWE5003 Engineering Big Data, and more. The exams will take place from May 13 to May 16, with each exam lasting from 6:30pm to 10:00pm. The timetable is subject to change due to unforeseen circumstances. This information is confidential and was last updated on March 19, 2025.

This document outlines the course schedule for the SE33 PT student intake for the Master of Technology in Software Engineering program at NUS. The course manager is Boon Kui and the dates for the first semester are listed as June 28 to October 11, 2025. The course will be held on Saturdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm and Wednesdays from 6:30pm to 10:00pm. The examination period is tentatively scheduled for the second week of November 2025. The course covers topics such as platform engineering, cloud native solution design, and architecting software solutions.
